During the visit of the Russian President, Dmitry Medvedev, to the United States, several joint statements were agreed upon between the two countries. These statements cover various topics including open government, Kyrgyzstan, energy efficiency, strategic stability, counterterrorism cooperation, inter-country adoption, Afghanistan, people-to-people connections, strategic partnership in innovation, Russia's accession to the World Trade Organization (WTO), and the U.S.-Russia Presidential Commission.